# Overview
This problem asks us to find the longest path (in terms of number of nodes visited) from node 1 to node n in a Directed Acyclic Graph (DAG), with the constraint that the total time taken should not exceed T. We use dynamic programming where dp[node][count] represents the minimum time to reach 'node' while visiting exactly 'count' nodes. We then find the maximum count where we can reach node n within time T, and backtrack to reconstruct the path.

<CODE>
